================================================================================
  THE 6-AGENT PIPELINE  (sequential, shared state)
================================================================================

  State enters as:  { wallet_address: "01abc..." }
  State exits  as:  all fields below populated


  +---------------------------------------------------------------------+
  |  [1] CREDIT AGENT   agents/credit_agent.py                          |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Fetches real on-chain wallet data from CSPR.cloud:                 |
  |                                                                     |
  |   cspr_cloud/wallet.py                                              |
  |    |- GET /accounts/{id}/transfers  ->  tx history                  |
  |    |- get_wallet_volume_summary()   ->  tx_count, counterparty_div  |
  |    |- get_flow_summary()            ->  CSPR inbound / outbound     |
  |    |- get_liquidity_positions()     ->  active DeFi positions       |
  |                                                                     |
  |   cspr_cloud/defi.py                                                |
  |    |- get_loan_records()            ->  loan history                |
  |    |- get_repayment_events()        ->  repayments made             |
  |    |- get_yield_events()            ->  staking/yield (DAO proxy)   |
  |    |- get_rwa_events()              ->  real-world asset activity   |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Computes 6 scoring dimensions (0-100 each):                        |
  |                                                                     |
  |   wallet_activity = floor(tx_count/2) + min(50, counterparty_div)   |
  |   repayment       = floor(repaid/loans * 100)  [50 if no loans]     |
  |   defi            = min(100, positions * 20)                        |
  |   income          = floor(inbound / (inbound+outbound) * 100)       |
  |   rwa             = min(100, rwa_events * 25)                       |
  |   dao             = min(100, yield_events * 15)                     |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Feeds dimensions into XGBoost model  ->  credit_score (0-1000)     |
  |  Runs SHAP explainability             ->  shap_breakdown            |
  |                                                                     |
  |  ERROR HANDLING: any CSPR.cloud failure -> all dimensions = 50      |
  |  (pipeline never halts, score degrades gracefully)                  |
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------+
                               |
                               v  + credit_score, sub_scores, shap_breakdown
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------+
  |  [2] RISK AGENT   agents/risk_agent.py                              |
  |                                                                     |
  |  XGBoost default probability prediction:                            |
  |   default_prob_30d  ->  base probability                            |
  |   default_prob_60d  ->  base x 1.5                                  |
  |   default_prob_90d  ->  base x 2.0                                  |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Score -> Tier mapping:                                             |
  |   750-1000  ->  A   (prime)                                         |
  |   600-749   ->  B   (near-prime)                                    |
  |   450-599   ->  C   (subprime)                                      |
  |   0-449     ->  D   (high risk)                                     |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Groq LLM (Llama 3.3 70B) enriches with:                            |
  |   early_warning_flags, narrative risk_analysis                      |
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------+
                               |
                               v  + risk_tier, default_prob_*, early_warning_flags
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------+
  |  [3] FRAUD AGENT   agents/fraud_agent.py                            |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Groq LLM analyzes raw_wallet_data for:                             |
  |   - wash trading patterns                                           |
  |   - circular transaction loops                                      |
  |   - sybil cluster indicators                                        |
  |   - fresh wallet risk (age < 7 days)                                |
  |   - low counterparty diversity                                      |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Outputs:  fraud_score (0-1),  fraud_flags[],  fraud_confidence     |
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------+
                               |
                               v  + fraud_score, fraud_flags
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------+
  |  [4] ATTESTATION AGENT   agents/attestation_agent.py                |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Groq LLM generates human-readable attestation_summary              |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Supabase:  save_attestation()  ->  stores full assessment record   |
  |              returns  attestation_hash  (Supabase record URL)       |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Casper (AURUM_DEPLOY_MODE=live):                                   |
  |   submitter.submit_contract_call() via casper-client put-deploy     |
  |   (bypasses contracts.py envelope layer, calls CLI directly)        |
  |                                                                     |
  |   CreditRegistry.issue_credit_score(caller, borrower, score, ...)   |
  |   ComplianceRegistry.issue_compliance_token(caller, borrower, ...)  |
  |                                                                     |
  |  NOTE: all contract entrypoints take an explicit "caller" string    |
  |  arg (deployer account-hash) as first argument.                     |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Outputs:  attestation_hash,  tx_hash,  deploy_mode                 |
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------+
                               |
                               v  + attestation_hash, tx_hash
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------+
  |  [5] MONITORING AGENT   agents/monitoring_agent.py                  |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Groq LLM decides whether credential stays active:                  |
  |   fraud_score > 0.5  ->  action = "revoke"                          |
  |   otherwise          ->  action = "maintain"                        |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Outputs:  credential_active (bool),  monitoring_action             |
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------+
                               |
                               v  + credential_active, monitoring_action
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------+
  |  [6] LENDING AGENT   agents/lending_agent.py                        |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Matches tier to lending pool offers:                               |
  |   A  ->  TrueFi  8%   up to $50,000                                 |
  |   B  ->  Maple   12%  up to $20,000                                 |
  |   C  ->  Clearpool 18% up to $5,000                                 |
  |   D  ->  no offers                                                  |
  |                                                                     |
  |  Groq LLM personalizes the lending_recommendation narrative         |
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------+
                               |
                               v
               Final response returned to client


================================================================================
  ORACLE QUERY  (x402-gated paid access)
================================================================================

  Any protocol can query a wallet's stored score without re-running the pipeline.
  Requires a valid x402 payment proof — mock or live depending on X402_MODE.


  Third-party protocol
        |
        |  GET /oracle/query?wallet=01abc...
        |  Header:  X-402-Payment-Proof: { ...proof JSON... }
        v
  +------------------------------------------------------------+
  |  routers/oracle.py                                         |
  |                                                            |
  |  1. Check X-402-Payment-Proof header present?              |
  |        NO  ->  HTTP 402 + payment_requirement JSON         |
  |                                                            |
  |  2. Parse proof JSON                                       |
  |        FAIL  ->  HTTP 402 + { error: invalid_proof_format} |
  |                                                            |
  |  3. X402Verifier.verify(proof)                             |
  |        Structural checks (both modes):                     |
  |          deadline not expired                              |
  |          receiver == treasury account                      |
  |          network matches                                   |
  |          nonce not replayed (in-memory cache)              |
  |          amount >= 1.5 CSPR                                |
  |        Live mode additional check:                         |
  |          verify_transfer_on_chain() scans last 20          |
  |          blocks for matching CSPR transfer to treasury     |
  |        FAIL  ->  HTTP 402 + error detail                   |
  |                                                            |
  |  4. Supabase: get_assessment(wallet)                       |
  |        NOT FOUND  ->  HTTP 404                             |
  |                                                            |
  |  5. Return credit profile                                  |
  |       { wallet_address, score, tier, shap_values,          |
  |         loan_offers, assessed_at }                         |
  +------------------------------------------------------------+

  Payment proof structure (JSON in header):
  {
    "payer_account":            "account-hash-...",
    "receiver_account":         "account-hash-e1b7...",   <- treasury
    "amount_cspr":              "1.50",
    "nonce":                    "uuid-or-random-string",
    "deadline_epoch_seconds":   1750000000,
    "network":                  "casper-test",
    "signature":                "...",
    "payment_reference":        "..."
  }

  X402_MODE=mock:  proof accepted on structure alone (no real CSPR needed)
  X402_MODE=live:  proof PLUS on-chain transfer verification required
                   payer must first send >= 1.5 CSPR to treasury account
                   server scans get-block-transfers on last 20 blocks

  NOTE: signature field is present in the proof schema but is NOT currently
  validated cryptographically. On-chain transfer presence is the live guard.
  Signature validation is a TODO before production.


================================================================================
  CRON MONITOR  (scheduled re-scoring)
================================================================================

  Called every 15 minutes (by Vercel cron or external scheduler).

  POST /cron/monitor
        |
        v
  Supabase: SELECT * FROM assessments WHERE credential_active = true
        |
        |  for each active wallet (sequential, rate-limit safe):
        v
  pipeline.invoke({ wallet_address })
        |
        |-- monitoring_action == "maintain"
        |         -> skip, no changes
        |
        +-- monitoring_action == "revoke"
                  |
                  |-- AURUM_DEPLOY_MODE=live:
                  |     submitter.submit_contract_call(
                  |       CreditRegistry, "revoke_credit_score",
                  |       { caller, borrower, revoked_at }
                  |     )  <- real put-deploy to testnet
                  |     on failure -> errored++, skip Supabase update
                  |
                  |-- AURUM_DEPLOY_MODE=mock:
                  |     skip chain call, log only
                  |
                  +-- Supabase: UPDATE credential_active = false

  Returns:
  {
    "status":               "ok",
    "credentials_checked":  N,
    "credentials_revoked":  N,
    "credentials_errored":  N,
    "deploy_mode":          "live" | "mock",
    "timestamp":            "2026-06-18T..."
  }


================================================================================
  API <-> CONTRACT RELATIONSHIPS
================================================================================

  4 Rust/Odra smart contracts deployed on Casper testnet.
  Python layer calls them through casper/contracts.py + casper/deploy_submitter.py

  All contract entrypoints take a "caller" string arg (deployer account-hash).
  Write entrypoints: submitted as real put-deploy via casper-client CLI.
  Read entrypoints:  submitted as getter deploys; return value parsed from
                     execution effects (WriteCLValue in transforms).


  casper/contracts.py  (AurumContracts)              Casper Testnet
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    |
    |-- issue_credit_score(caller, borrower, ...) --> CreditRegistry
    |   update_score(caller, borrower, ...)           env: CREDIT_REGISTRY_CONTRACT_HASH
    |   revoke_credit_score(caller, borrower, ...)    (fallback: CREDIT_REGISTRY_HASH)
    |   get_credit_score(borrower)                    |
    |     [live: call_getter get_score + get_tier      entrypoints:
    |            + is_credential_active_at]             issue_credit_score
    |                                                   update_score
    |                                                   revoke_credit_score
    |                                                   get_score
    |                                                   get_tier
    |                                                   get_attestation_hash
    |                                                   get_history_count
    |                                                   is_credential_active_at
    |
    |-- issue_compliance_token(caller, borrower, ...) -> ComplianceRegistry
    |   is_compliant(borrower, now)                    env: COMPLIANCE_REGISTRY_CONTRACT_HASH
    |     [live: call_getter is_compliant]             (fallback: COMPLIANCE_REGISTRY_HASH)
    |                                                   entrypoints:
    |                                                   issue_compliance_token
    |                                                   is_compliant
    |
    |-- query_credit_profile(borrower, proof) -------> OraclePaywall
    |   bulk_query(borrowers, proofs)                  env: ORACLE_PAYWALL_CONTRACT_HASH
    |     [live: call_getter query_credit_profile]     (fallback: ORACLE_PAYWALL_HASH)
    |     [oracle router uses Supabase as primary      entrypoints:
    |      cache; this is cross-validation]             query_credit_profile
    |                                                   bulk_query
    |
    +-- attest_reputation(caller, borrower, ...) ----> ReputationRegistry
        get_reputation(borrower)                       env: REPUTATION_REGISTRY_CONTRACT_HASH
          [live: call_getter get_reputation]           (fallback: REPUTATION_REGISTRY_HASH)
                                                        entrypoints:
                                                        attest_reputation
                                                        get_reputation


  casper/deploy_submitter.py  (DeploySubmitter)
   |- submit_contract_call()   -> casper-client put-deploy --session-hash <hex>
   |- check_deploy_status()    -> casper-client get-transaction (fallback get-deploy)
   |- call_getter()            -> submit_contract_call() + poll 60s + _extract_return_value()
   |- _extract_return_value()  -> parse WriteCLValue from execution effects (reversed scan)
   |- verify_transfer_on_chain() -> get-node-status + get-block-transfers (last 20 blocks)
   |- loaded via load_submitter_from_env()
   |    requires: CASPER_RPC_URL, CASPER_DEPLOY_CHAIN_NAME, CASPER_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH
   +- CASPER_CLIENT_BIN overrides binary path (default: "casper-client")
      example: /home/kuwarte/.cargo/bin/casper-client

  casper/x402.py  (X402Verifier)
   |- verify()  mock mode: structural checks only (deadline, receiver, nonce, amount)
   |- verify()  live mode: structural checks + verify_transfer_on_chain()
   |- nonce cache: in-memory Set (cleared on server restart — TODO: persist in Supabase)
   +- loaded via load_x402_verifier_from_env()


