================================================================================
  TESTING GUIDE
================================================================================

  Start the API:
    cd api && .venv/bin/uvicorn main:app --reload

  Score a real wallet (full e2e, mints on-chain):
    curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/assess \
      -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
      -d '{"wallet_address": "e1b7c78127d7b8b652ec00dd074a74bd47b5a9eebe1fd94cec3bb3e2ce7d8dad"}'

  Query oracle with mock payment (X402_MODE=mock):
    curl "http://localhost:8000/oracle/query?wallet=<wallet>" \
      -H 'X-402-Payment-Proof: {"payer_account":"account-hash-<payer>",
          "receiver_account":"account-hash-e1b7c78127d7b8b652ec00dd074a74bd47b5a9eebe1fd94cec3bb3e2ce7d8dad",
          "amount_cspr":"1.50","nonce":"unique-nonce-1",
          "deadline_epoch_seconds":9999999999,"network":"casper-test",
          "signature":"mock-signature","payment_reference":"mock:1"}'

  Switch to live x402 payments:
    1. Send >= 1.5 CSPR to treasury (account-hash-e1b7c7...) from any testnet wallet
    2. Set X402_MODE=live in api/.env
    3. Build proof JSON with your payer account-hash and a fresh nonce
    4. Server scans last 20 blocks to confirm transfer

  Run existing test scripts:
    .venv/bin/python test_scripts/test_e2e.py           # full pipeline
    .venv/bin/python test_scripts/test_deploy_live.py   # single contract call
    .venv/bin/python test_scripts/test_contract_integration.py


================================================================================
  KNOWN LIMITATIONS / TODOS
================================================================================

  - DeFi dimensions (defi, dao, rwa) score 0 in live mode because CSPR.cloud
    testnet has no confirmed loan/yield/RWA endpoints yet. Transfer history
    (wallet_activity, income, repayment) works live today.

  - x402 signature field in proof is not cryptographically validated.
    On-chain transfer scan is the live payment guard.  Add EdDSA signature
    verification before production.

  - x402 nonce cache is in-memory -- server restart clears replay protection.
    TODO: persist nonces in Supabase before production.

  - call_getter() costs real CSPR gas (put-deploy) and takes ~60s to poll.
    For high-frequency reads, cache results in Supabase or Redis.
    The oracle router already uses Supabase as the primary low-latency cache.

  - casper-client put-deploy is deprecated in v5; it still works for Odra v1
    contracts (hash- addresses). Migration to put-transaction invocable-entity
    requires upgrading contracts to Casper v2 entity model first.

  - API is local only (localhost:8000). To make publicly accessible, deploy
    to Render / Railway / VPS and update CORS origins in main.py.

  - Agent keypairs all share the deployer key. Generate separate keys per
    agent before mainnet (keys/ directory already has per-agent key files).
